# Line-ending policy.
#
# Normalize every text file to LF both in the repository AND in the working
# tree. This project builds Linux containers and deploys to Linux (Proxmox/k3s),
# so LF everywhere prevents cross-platform breakage. The classic failure this
# avoids: a CRLF line ending in a shell script appends a stray \r, which breaks
# the shebang/commands once the script runs inside a Linux container.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Explicit safety net for files where CRLF would be fatal at runtime.
# (Already covered by the wildcard above, but stated for clarity.)
*.sh        text eol=lf
Dockerfile* text eol=lf

# Binary files: never alter their bytes.
*.png binary
*.ico binary
*.jpg binary
